@Node "What" "Yes, tell me, what is it for ???"
@Prev "Main"

@{B}Pause @{UB} is a tiny command that waits until the user presses the
<RETURN> key or the <ENTER> key.

The command is most likely to be used in scripts after another command, with
extensive output, so the user has a chance to read the output, before the
script continues.

@{B}Pause@{UB} can be interrupted by pressing <CTRL-C> if you feel a strong
need for doing that. Interrupting the program in this way will return an
error code of 304, the standard AmigaDOS 'ERROR_BREAK' code.

@EndNode

@Node Features

How unlikely it may seem, @{B}Pause@{UB} does have features.

1. @{B}Pause@{UB} is public domain, the source code is distributed with the
   program. So anybody can change it to suit their needs.

2. @{B}Pause@{UB} is localized

3. @{B}Pause@{UB} is breakable
   (That feature is perhaps not very usefull for a program like @{B}Pause@{UB}
   but I still consider it a feature)

@EndNode

